  <title>Sharepoint Hide Ribbon</title>
  <description />
  <content>&lt;p&gt;To hide the ribbon nav bar from your html you can get use of these two ways;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First way&lt;/strong&gt; add the below css class to your css file&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="brush: css; first-line: 1; tab-size: 4; toolbar: false; "&gt;#s4-ribbonrow {
    display: none;
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Second way&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;use javascript to hide it&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="brush: js; first-line: 1; tab-size: 4; toolbar: false; "&gt;&amp;lt;script type="text/javascript"&amp;gt; document.getElementById("s4-ribbonrow").style.display = "none"; &amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;&lt;/pre&gt;</content>
